Staff Spotlight

At JPS, I get to see great kids grow into incredible adults while working alongside colleagues who inspire me every day with their collaboration, creativity, and passion.

- Brian Porter, JMS Science Teacher

What makes our district unique are the wide variety of opportunities we provide for students. From academics and athletics to fine arts and hands-on programs, every student can find a place to connect, grow, and thrive.

Non-Discrimination Statement

  • Jenks Public Schools prohibits discrimination in its education programs and activities, admission programs of students, recruitment, selection and/or employment on the basis of race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender expression, gender identity, genetic information, pregnancy, age, national origin, veteran status, or disability. The District provides equal access to designated youth groups, including Boy Scouts of America. Jenks Public Schools complies with federal and state regulations for implementing Title IX of the Education Amendment of 1972, Title VI, The Age Discrimination Act, Section 504, and Title II of the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA).

  • Board Policy 1.30 Non-Discrimination Statement
